be.ac.ulb.infof307.g01.client.controller.map

Class MapController

  • java.lang.Object
    • be.ac.ulb.infof307.g01.client.controller.map.MapController

  • public class MapController
extends Object
    Creates and controls the map view. This class is responsible for creating markers at startup and handling map-related events. It holds an instance of MarkerController, and passes it messages related to marker creation and edition.

        public void mapClicked(double latitude,
                       double longitude)
        Creates a marker creation popup and its controller. If a blocking PopUp already exists, does nothing.
        Parameters:
        latitude - the latitude at which the marker has to be created
        longitude - the longitude at which the marker has to be created

      • markerClicked

        public void markerClicked(int markerId)
        Creates a marker edition or information popup and its controller. If the marker was created by the current user, an edition popup appears. Otherwise an information popup is used instead. If a blocking PopUp already exists, does nothing.
        Parameters:
        markerId - the ID of the marker to edit or display
